            "title": "Game Systems (Epistemological Practice)",
            "summary": "Game (epistemological practice) vs. Education (stable a priori object): Game is the only way education can exist in a crisis. State (reproduction of difference) and Man (basic unit of time): When time no longer repeats, man will experience all kinds of malfunctions again. Revolution (rupture&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<p>Game (epistemological practice) vs. Education (stable a priori object): Game is the only way education can exist in a crisis.<br><br>State (reproduction of difference) and Man (basic unit of time): When time no longer repeats, man will experience all kinds of malfunctions again.<br><br>Revolution (rupture of time) vs. Theory (a priori practice): Theory and reality rupture before they even occur.<br><br>Time (the unfolding of existence) and folding (connectivity): Accelerating and doubling the repetitive practice of itself.<br><br>Future (inconsistency of time) vs. Reality (uniqueness of existence): The doubling future will split.<br><br>Capital (emptiness itself) vs. History (failure of time): De-selfified time.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/30/W020220113028361891078_result-2.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"684\" height=\"684\"></figure>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
