        {
            "id": "https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/regional-map.html",
            "url": "https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/regional-map.html",
            "title": "Regional map",
            "summary": "Northwest Meat Processing Center (2036) Surface Layer (Surface Observation) I. Flesh Sector Semi-open \"meat curtain sheds,\" dripping with moisture when the wind blows. Automatic slicing towers, their shadows visible through transparent walls. Raw meat transport tracks span the ground like an aerial light rail system.",
            "content_html": "<p>Northwest Meat Processing Center (2036)</p>\n<p><br>Surface Layer (Surface Observation)<br>I. Flesh Sector</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-22T20-38-51.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-22T20-38-51-xs.jpg 640w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-22T20-38-51-sm.jpg 768w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-22T20-38-51-md.jpg 1024w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-22T20-38-51-lg.jpg 1366w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-22T20-38-51-xl.jpg 1600w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-22T20-38-51-2xl.jpg 1920w\"></figure>\n<p><br>Semi-open \"meat curtain sheds,\" dripping with moisture when the wind blows.<br>Automatic slicing towers, their shadows visible through transparent walls.<br>Raw meat transport tracks span the ground like an aerial light rail system.<br>Heavy metal decryption, covered in meat stains and unknown handprints.<br>Abandoned meat tank area, one tank resembling a tomb.<br>High-pitched diagnostic column, specifically monitoring \"body escape incidents.\"<br>Meat notification board (like a bulletin board but filled with tissue structures).<br><br>II. Feeding-Excretion Center</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-05-53.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-05-53-xs.jpg 640w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-05-53-sm.jpg 768w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-05-53-md.jpg 1024w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-05-53-lg.jpg 1366w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-05-53-xl.jpg 1600w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-05-53-2xl.jpg 1920w\"></figure>\n<p><br>A circular complex, with a huge feeding area in the center. Well<br>A rotating elbow-shaped passageway connecting food and waste disposal<br>A \"feedback pool\" of transparent liquid, with splashes resembling radial patterns<br>\"Food indicators\" scrolling on a gray-white tower<br>A large, blocked waste pipe overflowing, forming a support mound<br><br>III. Liquid Zone (Liquid Processing Zone)</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-28-50.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-28-50-xs.jpg 640w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-28-50-sm.jpg 768w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-28-50-md.jpg 1024w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-28-50-lg.jpg 1366w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-28-50-xl.jpg 1600w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-28-50-2xl.jpg 1920w\"></figure>\n<p><br>A huge ground-level liquid reservoir (semi-transparent bulge)<br>A corridor where workers disappear into a liquid mist<br>A large pump tower beating like a heart<br>A strange \"liquid pattern\" surface with muddy but removable metal and glass<br>Pipes covering the entire open space like vines<br><br>IV. Human Sector</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-01-28.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-01-28-xs.jpg 640w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-01-28-sm.jpg 768w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-01-28-md.jpg 1024w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-01-28-lg.jpg 1366w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-01-28-xl.jpg 1600w ,https://ochaaaaaaa.github.io/media/posts/25/responsive/digicamfx-jpegSimulation-2026-04-23T02-01-28-2xl.jpg 1920w\"></figure>\n<p><br>Abandoned workers' dormitories<br>A commune's propaganda board, but the content is unusually blurry<br>An old, looping broadcast in the queuing hall<br>A dilapidated tin canteen with long tables resembling operating tables<br><br>Underground and Internal Zone (Substructure and Facilities)<br><br>(To be supplemented)<br>Incident Spots<br><br>(To be supplemented)</p>",
            "author": {
                "name": "Victor_nick"
